display.shortDescription: A forgiving modern espresso profile, able to do PSPH or Soup styles, depending on grind size.
display.description: Originally described by DC on EAF Discord.  Modern style shot at an ~1:2.5-3 ratio with a very coarse grind, gentle puck saturation, followed by fast water flow (~8-12 sec). Intended for light to wheatgrass roast coffees and results in the cup are similar to filter coffee but with much more intense acidity.  Aims:  shoot for a peak of 1 to 5 bar pressure for PSPH, and max 1 bar pressure for Soup.  If you go over, you've ground too finely.  This is a unique profile which can do both, and has a very large forgiving pressure window.  Aim for high teens for shot duration.
